  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The same number of sacrifices as at the new moon were to be offered on every one of the seven days of the feast of unleavened bread (Mazzoth), from the 15th to the 21st of the month, whereas there was no general festal offering on the day of the Passover, or the 14th of the month (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 12:3-14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). With regard to the feast of Mazzoth, the rule is repeated from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 12:15-20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 23:6-8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", that on the first and seventh day there was to be a Sabbath rest and holy meeting. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
